genresAdvancedInfo.name: western saharan folk
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This genre of music is characterized by the use of traditional instruments such as the tinde drum and the tidinit guitar. The music often tells stories of the nomadic lifestyle of the Saharan people and their struggles with displacement and political unrest. The melodies are hauntingly beautiful and the rhythms are complex, reflecting the rich cultural heritage of the region.
